description: Mixed development on land formerly occupied by all buildings to the south of the South Mall and the erection of: a) a 14 screen cinema complex (6,670 sq.m.) over new retail units (8855 sq.m.) and food and drink units (3,625 sq.m.); b) a seven-storey car park with 957 parking spaces (96 spaces for residents parking) and 229 cycle parking spaces (144 for residents use); c) a part eight, part twenty-three-storey block at the southern end of the site comprising food and drink/retail floorspace, entrance lobby to flats, stores, sub-station and plant room in basement, access and egress to car park, and cycle stores at ground level and 145 dwellings with amenity decks above; d) formation of a pedestrian link to King Georges Park;  e) alterations to alignment of Mapleton Crescent and other highway works around junction of Neville Gill Close and Mapleton Road and resurfacing Neville Gill Close to west of proposed block of flats;
